parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the engine crank but does not start
the ignition coil is fried
the ignition control module needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The fuse box melts or catches fire
the vehicle's speed reduces
smoke appears under the hood
the gauges fluctuate
warning lights and interior lights flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag sensor turns off and on
the airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag does not deploy during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause accidents or injuries, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights suddenly quit working
the low beam relay is burnt beyond recognition
the fuse box is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the remote start system can cause inconvenience and frustration for the driver.
symptoms: The remote start system quits working
the system disappears from the vehicle's DIC.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft deterrent system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and frustration for the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
even after reset procedures
the system fails to recognize and enable vehicle keys.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Low beam headlights turn off randomly while driving
sometimes accompanied by the failure of daytime running lights; headlights may work intermittently or not at all; high beams and fog lights may still function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of daytime running lights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during the day or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Daytime running lights stay on even when the car is turned off
draining the battery; daytime running lights fail to turn on or turn off intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal switch can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering, brakes, and acceleration, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
accompanied by a loss of power steering
brakes
and acceleration; the vehicle restarts after a few minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jerks when accelerating
decelerating
or shifting gears; the vehicle hesitates or stalls; the transmission makes a loud clunking or shuttering noise; the vehicle vibrates or shakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage or disengage; the vehicle does not move when in gear; the transmission makes a loud noise or vibrates excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "Reduced Engine Power" message; the vehicle slows down or loses power; the vehicle hesitates or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The gear shift cable failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shift cable breaks or wears out; the vehicle continues to roll after shifting into park; the vehicle cannot be started due to the gear shift cable failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injury or death, as occupants may not receive the necessary protection to prevent harm.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
even when the vehicle sustains significant damage
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent airbag warning light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which may lead to airbag failure in a crash, putting occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard comes on and off intermittently
indicating a potential problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty passenger airbag sensor can prevent the airbag from deploying in a crash, putting the passenger at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag sensor light comes on
indicating that the airbag may not deploy in a crash
or the airbag fails to deploy even when an adult passenger is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes fail to respond
or the vehicle loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
or the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
